**Purpose:** cloud orchestrator + local worker + cloud investigator three-role flow. Skip this entire section if the project is not using the orchestrator pattern.

**You should have:**
- `docs/ORCHESTRATION_MAP.md` — three-role split
- `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md` — Level 1/2/3 scenario guide before selecting cloud/local responsibilities
- `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` — 9-step worker loop, MAX_ITERATIONS by Packet Class
- `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md` — packet template with Packet Class + Concreteness Tier
- `docs/WORKER_RESULT_PACKET.md` — result template with self-review + regression-accretion fields
- `docs/APPLY_CHECKLIST.md` — worker pre-return ritual (do not confuse with the *template* `APPLY_CHECKLIST.md`)
- `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` — mandatory cloud-orchestrator review of every DONE packet
- `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` — escalation role
- `docs/OPERATOR_DASHBOARD.md` — plain-English operator choices, rollback, and tie-breaker options
- `AI_AGENT.md` § Orchestrator Rails populated (10 hard rules, decision tree, unattended run rules)

**Copy from:** the asus repo (`/home/mamana/private-repos/asus/docs/`) is the reference implementation; or a known-good orchestrator-pattern project.

**Triggers to register in `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md` § Event Triggers:**
- "Before choosing Level 1/2/3 AI workflow mode" → `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md`
- "Starting template retrofit on an existing project" → `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md` and `docs/TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH.md`
- "Migrating Firebase/cloud app to local server" → `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/TECH_STACK.md`, `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md`, and `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md`
- "Planning overnight local-agent run" → `docs/SCENARIO_PLAYBOOK.md`, `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md`, and `docs/STATE_LEDGER_PROTOCOL.md`
- "Issuing a worker packet" → `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md`
- "Worker returned DONE" → `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` (mandatory review)
- "Worker returned BLOCKED twice on same Path ID" → `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md`
- "About to run unattended overnight" → `AI_AGENT.md` § Unattended Run Rules

**Proves it works:** dry-run a packet end-to-end on a trivial change.
- [ ] All docs present, rails populated, triggers registered, or N/A:

**Orchestrator readiness audit:** before using local models for most implementation, confirm the project has enough rails that the local worker can succeed without a human reading raw diffs.
- [ ] Every worker packet names Path IDs, allowed files, commands, smoke tests, stop conditions, and rollback expectations.
- [ ] Scenario playbook is present and routes template retrofit, Firebase/cloud-to-local migration, overnight local-agent work, and high-risk work to the right Level 1/2/3 mode.
- [ ] Vague human directives trigger multiple-choice clarification before broad specs or worker packets are written.
- [ ] Every DONE packet requires RED/GREEN evidence, changed files, tests run, unresolved risks, and local self-review.
- [ ] Test-honesty review rejects tautology tests and requires assertions tied to real behavior or user/data outcomes.
- [ ] Cloud orchestrator review checks traceability, test honesty, security posture, and user workflow impact before accepting DONE.
- [ ] UI-visible packets require a manual click path, screenshot/trace, or browser-smoke evidence before DONE.
- [ ] Data-mutating packets require a pre-change snapshot/dump or explicit N/A rationale and operator-executable restore steps.
- [ ] Cloud investigator escalation is triggered by repeated BLOCKED status, uncertain architecture, auth/security ambiguity, or failing CI after local green.
- [ ] Investigator protocol halts with `TIE-BREAKER-HALT` after two unresolved investigator cycles on the same Path ID.
- [ ] Operator dashboard or handoff format gives the non-coder operator decisions and evidence, not raw diff interpretation.
- [ ] Operator dashboard includes data snapshot/restore fields and three plain-English tie-breaker choices.

