## 8) Final Adoption Gate

Run in order; all must pass:

1. `bash scripts/verify.sh` (or project verify gate) — exit 0
2. `bash scripts/check_template_drift.sh . path/to/templates-v2` — exit 0
3. `bash scripts/validate_context_budget.sh` — exit 0 for routed startup profiles
4. `scripts/validate_templates.sh` (if present) — exit 0
5. Required security scans pass locally or are confirmed green in CI
6. Runtime smoke required mode passes for pre-beta/beta projects
7. Orchestrator-pattern repos confirm vague-prompt pushback, anti-tautology review, UI smoke evidence, data snapshot/restore, and tie-breaker halt are wired into the relevant docs
8. Complete `docs/TEMPLATE_VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.md` — every box checked
9. Push a no-op commit; confirm CI green
10. Update `CHANGELOG.md` `Unreleased`: "Adopted templates-v2 vN.N via TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH; sections completed: ..."

- [ ] All ten pass.

Adoption is complete when this box is checked. Until then, the AI should treat the project as *partially adopted* and surface unchecked sections at the start of every session.
